name: The Case of the Hopeless Diamond
To Bee or Not to Bee
Snow White and the 7 Treasure Hunters

description:
Japanese title: Shinigami VS shinigami! Bōsō suru Chikara, 死神VS死神！暴走する力.

Kariya and the others successfully open the Seireimon using the mobs from Kusajishi. Upon entering, they attack not only the Soul Reaper guards, but the mobs as well—and confusion reigns.
name: Shinigami vs. Shinigami! The Uncontrollable Power

description:
Japanese title: Soifon Shisu? Onmitsukidō no Saigo, 砕蜂死す？隠密機動の最後.

Soi Fon is poisoned by a member of her punishment force, which is under Ritze’s control. Having increased her power, Ritze now can control several Soul Reapers at a time.
name: Soi Fong Dies? The Last of the Special Forces

description:
Japanese title: Mayuri Bankai!! Sawatari: Akuma no Gekitotsu (マユリ卍解!!沢渡・悪魔の激突)

Sawatari enters the Seireitei and sees Mayuri Kurotsuchi, the captain of Squad 12. Mayuri proposes that he become a guinea pig for an experiment, but Sawatari refuses and attacks Mayuri using the Doll Baura.
name: Mayuri's Bankai!! Sawatari: Clash of the Demon

description:
Japanese title: Saigo no Kuinshī! Bōhatsu suru Chikara" (最後のクインシー！暴発する力).

The battle between the Soul Reapers and Bounts intensifies. Kariya suddenly appears at the Department of Research and Development, where he looks for an original crest of the Bount in the bureau and interrogates Nemu.
name: The Last Quincy! The Exploding Power

description:
Japanese title: Ishida, Genkai o Koete Ute! (石田、限界を超えて撃て！)

Uryu is severely injured by Nieder’s attack but tries desperately to counterattack, though his bow seems to have run out of power. Yoshi thoroughly revels in the fight in the Soul Society because she can do whatever she wants.
name: Ishida, Exceeding the Limits to Attack!

description:
Japanese title: Shitō Jūbantai! Hyōrinmaru o Hanate (死闘十番隊！氷輪丸を放て)

The Soul Reapers of Squad 10 find Koga. Hitsugaya, with all the Soul Reapers of Squad 10, use Kurahito’s Bount sensor and tries to capture Koga, who flees the Seireitei.
name: 10th Division's Death Struggle! The Release of Hyourinmaru

description:
Japanese title: Kariya! Bakuhatsu e no Kauntodaun (狩矢！爆発へのカウントダウン)

Captain Hitsugaya has defeated Koga, leaving Jin Kariya as the last surviving Bount.
name: Kariya! Countdown to the Detonation

description:
Japanese title: Inochi to Fukushū! Ishida, Kyūkyoku no Sentaku (命と復讐！石田、究極の選択)

During the battle between Jin Kariya and Rantao, Karyia learns the origin of his powers.
name: Life and Revenge! Ishida, the Ultimate Choice

description:
Japanese title: Furiorosareta Yaiba! Hametsu no Shunkan (振り下ろされた刃！破滅の瞬間)

Ichigo arrives just in time, as Uryu and Rantao struggle to fend off Jin Kariya. Captain Hitsugaya and the others try to go after Ichigo, but Rantao stops them.
name: The Swung-Down Edge! The Moment of Ruin

description:
Japanese title: Dōkoku no Baunto! Saigo no Gekitotsu (慟哭のバウント！最後の激突)

Ichigo and Kariya's final clash begins on Sokyoku hill. Ichigo realizes that Kariya's fighting style consists of counterattacks that rely on his incredible ability to recover.
name: The Wailing Bount! The Last Clash

description:
Japanese title: Ichigo to Rukia, Kaiten suru Omoi (一護とルキア、廻天する想い)

It has been a few days since Kariya was defeated, and all of the Jokai Crests have been sealed away. Ichigo and his friends rest until the Senkaimon is prepared so that they can return to the World of the Living.
name: Ichigo and Rukia, Thoughts Revolving Around Heaven

description:
Japanese title: Daikōgyō Saikai! Kyōfu no Tenkōsei (代行業再開！恐怖の転校生)

It’s back to high school and Hollow slaying for Ichigo Kurosaki, who is now officially recognized as a Substitute Soul Reaper by the Soul Society.
name: Reopening of the Substitute Business! The Terrifying Transfer Student

description: When the Titans try to get Beast Boy to clean his room, they discover that there's more to garbage than just trash.
name: Hot Garbage

description: In order to fend off a vicious attack, John (Matt Ryan) summons a demon into himself. Chas (Charles Halford), Zed (Angelica Celaya) and Anne Marie (guest star Claire van der Boom) race against time to save John before it's too late.
name: The Saint of Last Resorts: Part 2

has_staff_review.name: Constantine Episode #109 - The Saint of Last Resorts Part 2

description: Leonard Snart AKA Captain Cold (guest star Wentworth Miller) returns to Central City with a new hotheaded partner in tow -- Mick Rory AKA Heat Wave (guest star Dominic Purcell). The duo plan to steal a multi-million dollar painting, but Cold has another agenda while in town -- to set a trap for The Flash. Snart and Mick kidnap someone close to The Flash and threaten to kill them unless The Flash shows up for a battle of fire and ice. Barry tells Joe (Jesse L. Martin) he isn't sure he should take on Snart again after the casualties that happened the last time they fought. Meanwhile, Barry asks Dr. Wells (Tom Cavanagh), Caitlin (Danielle Panabaker) and Cisco (Carlos Valdes) to help him double his training efforts so he's ready for the Reverse Flash when he returns to Central City. Iris (Candice Patton) deals with the aftermath of Barry's confession, and Cisco makes the CCPD a new shield.
name: Revenge of the Rogues

has_staff_review.name: The Flash Episode #110 - "Revenge of the Rogues"

description: In the aftermath of Oliver's (Stephen Amell) fight with Ra's al Ghul (Matt Nable), Diggle (David Ramsey) and Arsenal (Colton Haynes) continue to protect the city in the Arrow's absence. However, after three days without hearing from Oliver, they begin to fear the worst may have happened to their friend. Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) refuses to believe that Oliver could be dead until Merlyn (John Barrowman) pays the team a surprise visit. Thea (Willa Holland) suspects there is something more behind Oliver's disappearance and asks Merlyn for a favor. Meanwhile, Ray (Brandon Routh) tests a part of his new suit and Laurel (Katie Cassidy) takes up the mantle of the Black Canary.
name: Left Behind

description:
Japanese title: Kyōgaku! Oyajitachi no Shōtai (驚愕！親父達の正体)

Uryu is attacked by a Menos Grande and is saved by his father, Ryuken. Ryuken defeats the Menos with a single attack. He tells Uryu that he can help him regain his powers but only under Ryuken’s conditions.
name: Shock! The Fathers' True Identity

description:
Japanese title: Tatakai no Hajimari, Vaizādo to Arankaru (戦いの始まり、仮面の軍勢と破面)

Isshin Kurosaki shows up in his Soul Reaper form and defeats Grand Fisher with a single strike. When Kisuke Urahara appears, Isshin and Kisuke discuss the fact that Sosuke Aizen has made contact with Hollows...
name: The Commencement of War, the Vizards and the Arrancars

description:
Japanese title: Sekai Hōkai e no Jokyoku, Arankaru Shūrai (世界崩壊への序曲、アランカル襲来！)

Ichigo senses that the hollow within him is getting stronger and fears that he’ll be swallowed whole in his current state.
name: Prelude to the Apocalypse, The Arrancar's Offensive

description:
Japanese title: Saikai, Ichigo to Rukia to Shinigami-tachi (再会、一護とルキア)

Orihime and Chad are in danger and Ichigo rushes to their aid. He immediately uses his Bankai and clashes with the brutish Arrancar, Yammy.
name: Reunion, Ichigo and Rukia and Soul Reapers

description:
Japanese title: Tokumei! Yatte Kita Shinigami-tachi (特命！やってきた死神たち)

Rukia, Renji, Ikkaku, Yumichika, Captain Hitsugaya and Rangiku have come to the World of the Living and they have found Ichigo still feeling depressed about his poor performance in the fight against the Arrancars.
name: Mission! The Shinigami Who Came

description:
Japanese title: Ashiki Hitomi, Aizen Futatabi (悪しき瞳、藍染再び)

Ulquiorra and Yammy have returned to the Hollow World, Hueco Mundo. They report to Sosuke Aizen and twenty other Arrancars about their fight with Ichigo and his friends.
name: The Evil Eye, Aizen Returns

description:
Japanese title: Rukia Sentō Kaishi! Kōritsuku Shiroi Yaiba (ルキア戦闘開始！凍りつく白い刃)

The Arrancar, Grimmjow, has entered the World of the Living and he has brought a group of minions from Hueco Mundo with him. The Arrancars’ goal is to kill anyone who possesses the slightest amount of spiritual pressure.
name: Rukia's Battle Commences! The Freezing White Blade

description:
Japanese title: Ikkaku Bankai! Subete o Kudaku Chikara (一角卍解！全てを砕く力).

Ikkaku and the Arrancar, Edrad, have a fierce battle in the streets of Karakura Town. Yumichika stands aside and watches because he knows that Ikkaku will be furious if he interferes.
name: Ikkaku's Bankai! The Power That Breaks Everything

description:
Japanese title: Zaraki Tai Hiwa! Tsuite iru Otokotachi (更木隊秘話！ツイている男たち)

Ikkaku releases his Bankai, Ryumon Hozukimaru, which he has kept a secret for some time. He clashes with Edrad, who shows his true power by releasing his zanpakuto.
name: Zaraki Division's Secret Story! The Lucky Men

description:
Japanese title: Hitsugaya Chiru! Kudaketa Hyōrinmaru (日番谷散る！砕けた氷輪丸)

The Soul Reapers struggle against the might of the Arrancars. Despite the Arrancar Shawlong’s overwhelming strength, Captain Hitsugaya continues his attacks.
name: Hitsugaya Scatters! The Broken Hyōrinmaru

description:
Japanese title: Gekitotsu! Mamoru Mono VS Kōmuru Mono (激突！護る者VS被る者)

The Soul Reapers receive permission from the Soul Society to use Gentei Kaijo, a spiritual pressure restriction release.
name: Clash! The Protector vs. The Bearer

description:
Japanese title: Vaizādo! Mezameshi Monotachi no Chikara (ヴァイザード！目覚めし者たちの力)

Grimmjow is the only survivor of the Arrancars’ intense battle with the Soul Reapers. He returns with Tosen to Sosuke Aizen's palace, Las Noches in Hueco Mundo.
name: Vizard! The Power of the Awakened

description:
Japanese title: Ichigo, Kanzen Horō-ka!? (一護、完全ホロウ化!?)

Ichigo visits Shinji Hirako at the Visoreds’ hideout in order to find out how to control his inner Hollow. He tries to get an answer by force, but Hiyori Sarugaki interrupts his battle with Shinji.
name: Ichigo, Complete Hollowification?!

description:
Japanese title: Gekitotsu! Kuroi Bankai to Shiroi Bankai (激突！黒い卍解と白い卍解)

Ichigo has begun training with the Visoreds in order to learn how to suppress his inner hollow. He enters his inner world and is greeted by the mirror image of himself holding a white Zangetsu.
name: Collision! Black Bankai and the White Bankai

description:
Japanese title: Kinkyū Hōkoku! Aizen no Osorubeki Keikaku! (緊急報告！藍染の恐るべき計画)

Ichigo has entered his inner world and is blocking fierce attacks made by another Ichigo who wields a white Zangetsu. Ichigo is cornered as images of Byakuya Kuchiki and Jin Kariya pummel him into the ground.
name: Urgent Report! Aizen's Terrifying Plan

description:
Japanese title: Uryū VS Ryūken! Gekitotsu Kuinshī Oyako (雨竜VS竜弦！激突クインシー親子)

Sosuke Aizen’s ultimate goal of killing the Soul King has been revealed.
name: Uryū vs. Ryūken! Clash of the Parent-Child Quincys

description:
Japanese title: Urahara no Ketsudan, Orihime no Omoi (浦原の決断、織姫の想い)

Ichigo and his friends undergo exhaustive training in preparation for the upcoming winter showdown with Sosuke Aizen.
name: Urahara's Decision, Orihime's Thoughts

description:
Japanese title: Akumu no Arankaru! Hitsugayatai Shutsugeki (悪夢のアランカル！日番谷隊出撃)

Captain Hitsugaya's advance troops remain in Karakura Town to prepare for the showdown with Sosuke Aizen. Rangiku is fascinated by life in the world of the living, and she finds it impossible to devote her time to training.
name: The Nightmare Arrancar! Team Hitsugaya Moves Out

description:
Japanese title: Maiorita Yami no Shisha! Zōshoku suru Akui (舞い降りた闇の使者！増殖する悪意)

Captain Hitsugaya's advance troops remain in Karakura Town to prepare for the showdown with Sosuke Aizen. Rangiku is fascinated by life in the world of the living, and she finds it impossible to devote her time to training.
name: The Swooping Descent of the Dark Emissary! The Propagation of Malice

description:
Japanese title: Mienai Teki! Hitsugaya, Hijō na Ketsudan (見えない敵！日番谷、非情な決断)

Hitsugaya and his advanced troops learn that Shota’s little sister Yui was the Mock Arrancar’s first victim.
name: The Invisible Enemy! Hitsugaya's Merciless Decision

description:
Japanese title: Rangiku no Namida, Kanashiki Kyōdai no Wakare (乱菊の涙、哀しき兄妹の別れ)

It is revealed that the Mock Arrancar gained an explosive amount of strength when it devoured Yui and has reanimated her soul to use her as bait to lure and attack human souls.
name: Rangiku's Tears, the Sorrowful Parting of Brother and Sister

description:
Japanese title: Hitsugaya to Karin to Sakkā Bōru (日番谷と夏梨とサッカーボール)

When a bullying group of middle school students refuse to give up the soccer field, Karin Kurosaki fearlessly agrees to lead her reluctant friends into a soccer match against the upperclassmen.
name: Hitsugaya, Karin and Soccer Ball

description:
Japanese title: Ikkaku, Nekketsu Kendō Monogatari (一角、熱血剣道物語)

Karakura First High School's kendo team is ambushed, and the captain and all of the main members are seriously injured.
name: Ikkaku's Hot-Blooded Kendo Tale

description:
Japanese title: Utsukushiki Patishie, Yumichika! (美しきパティシエ、弓親！)

The Head Captain orders Mayuri Kurotsuchi to simplify the procedures to perform Gentei Kaijo, a restriction release for the Spiritual Pressure of the Advance Troops while in the World of the Living.
name: The Beautiful Patissier, Yumichika!

description:
Japanese title: Hakarareta, Kon! Rangiku wa Mite Ita... (はかられたコン！乱菊は見ていた…)

Kon, lonely and bored due to Rukia’s and Orihime’s absence, decides to pay a visit to Rangiku.
name: Kon is Deceived! Rangiku on the Lookout...

description:
Japanese title: Weko Mundo Nairan! Urukiora no Shi (ウェコムンド内乱！ウルキオラの死)

Trouble is brewing in Las Noches, Aizen's palace in the Hollow realm, Hueco Mundo. One of the Arrancars, Patras, rebels against Aizen and tries to steal the Hogyoku.
name: Civil War in Hueco Mondo! Ulquiorra's Death

description:
Japanese title: Akui no Tatakai, Aizen no Wana (悪意の戦い、藍染の罠)

Renji’s fight with Patras continues as it destroys Urahara's shop and parts of Karakura Town.
name: The Malicious Battle, Aizen's Trap

description:
Japanese title: Hueco Mundo Saidō! Hitsugaya VS Yammy (ウェコムンド再動！日番谷VSヤミー)

There are only a few months left until the showdown with the Arrancars. Ichigo continues to train with the Visoreds, but the amount of time in which he can remain Hollowfied hasn’t increased by much.
name: Hueco Mondo Moves Again! Hitsugaya vs. Yammy

description:
Japanese title: Ichigo VS Gurimujō, Jū-ichi Byō no tatakai! (一護VSグリムジョー、11秒の戦い)

Arrancars suddenly appear in the World of the Living. Yammy, Luppi, Grimmjow, and Wonderweiss are confronted by Hitsugaya's advance troops and Ichigo.
name: Ichigo vs. Grimmjow, the 11-Second Battle

description:
Japanese title: Sakubō no Urukiora, Taiyō ga Shizumu Toki (策謀のウルキオラ、太陽が沈む時)

Hitsugaya's advance troops continue to fight the Arrancars who appeared in Karakura Town. Urahara shows up to help.
name: Ulquiorra's Scheme, the Moment when the Sun Sets

description:
Japanese title: Sayonara..., Kurosaki-kun! (さようなら…、黒崎くん)

Ichigo and his friends manage to drive away Grimmjow and the other Arrancars. But behind the scenes, Aizen orders Ulquiorra to bring Orihime to Hueco Mundo.
name: Goodbye..., Kurosaki

description:
Japanese title: Genmei! Inoue Orihime no Kyushūtsu o Kinzu (厳命！井上織姫ノ救出ヲ禁ズ)

Ichigo awakens to realize that the serious injuries he received from Grimmjow's attack have completely healed. He senses that Orihime came to his room from the traces of Spiritual Pressure that she left behind.
name: Strict Order! The Forbidden Rescue of Orihime Inoue

description:
Japanese title: Fukkatsu no Gurimujō (復活のグリムジョー)

Orihime has been kidnapped by Sosuke Aizen and the Arrancars. Ichigo decides to go to Hueco Mundo in order to save her.
name: Grimmjow's Revival

description:
Japanese title: Ishida, Chado, Atarashiki Chikara To taidō (石田・チャド、新しき力の胎動)

Ichigo, Uryu, and Chad charge through the Garganta and into Hueco Mundo. There, they find themselves in a large corridor.
name: Ishida and Sado, The Quickening of a New Power

description:
Japanese title: Esupāda Shūketsu! Aizen no Gozen Kaigi (エスパーダ集結！藍染の御前会議)

Ichigo and his friends defeat the Arrancars Iceringer and Demora, whom they meet in Underground Pathway 22.
name: The Espada Gather! Aizen's Royal Assembly

description:
Japanese title: Sono Na wa Neru! Fushigi na Arankaru Tōjō (その名はネル！不思議なアランカル登場)

Ichigo and his friends save a girl who is being attacked by mysterious Arrancars.
name: The Name's Nel! The Appearance of a Strange Arrancar

description:
Japanese title: Menosu no Mori! Kieta Rukia o Sakase (メノスの森！消えたルキアを探せ)

Ichigo and his friends are swallowed by the desert of Hueco Mundo and fall into the Menos Forest, home of the Menos.
name: Forest of Menos! Search for the Missing Rukia

description:
Japanese title: Ashido, Kako kara Kita Shinigami (アシド、過去から来た死神)

Ichigo and his friends have fallen into the Menos Forest. They fight off attacks from Gillians while they look for Rukia and Nel, who have been separated from the group.
name: Ashido, The Soul Reaper Who Came from the Past

description:
Japanese title: Kuzureiku Mori, Hyakuman no Menosu (崩れ行く森、百万のメノス)

Ashido and Rukia continue to battle Pequenos, one of the Adjuchas who controls the Menos Forest.
name: Through the Crumbling Forest, a Million Menos

description:
Japanese title: Chikai! Futatabi Ikite Kono Basho e (誓い！再び生きてこの場所へ)

Ichigo and his friends arrive at Las Noches, Aizen's stronghold, where they break through a wall and charge into the palace.
name: Oath! Back Here Alive Again

description:
Japanese title: Fukiareru Bōfū! Odoru Arankaru to no Sōgū (吹き荒れる暴風！踊るアランカルとの遭遇)

Ichigo, Uryu, Chad, Rukia, and Renji go their separate ways down the corridors of Las Noches and vow to safely reunite.
name: The Raging Storm! Encounter with the Dancing Arrancar

description:
Japanese title: Ichigo Hangeki! Koitsu ga Ore no Bankai da (一護反撃！こいつが俺の卍解だ)

Dordoni the Arrancar is a Privaron Espada, a former Espada. Ichigo underestimates his strength and is quickly driven into a corner when Dordoni releases his Zanpakuto.
name: Ichigo Strikes Back! This Is My Bankai

description:
Japanese title: Akuma no Kenkyū! Zaeruaporo no Takurami (悪魔の研究！ザエルアポロの企み)

Dordoni makes a final attempt to win his battle, but he is defeated by a Hollowfied Ichigo.
name: The Devilish Research! Szayelaporro's Plan

description:
Japanese title: Rukia to Kaien, Kanashimi no Saikai (ルキアと海燕、哀しみの再会)

In the depths of Las Noches, Rukia encounters Ninth Espada Aaroniero Arruruerie in an area with a blue sky.
name: Rukia and Kaien, the Sorrowful Reunion

description:
Japanese title: Rukia Hangeki! Kesshi no Kidō o Hanate (ルキア反撃！決死の鬼道を放て)

Rukia is angered when Kaien tells her to hand over her friends in return for letting her go and is convinced that this Kaien is a fake.
name: Rukia Retaliates! Release the Desperate Kidou

description:
Japanese title: Ishida & Pesshe, Yūjō no Gattai Kōgeki (石田＆ペッシェ、友情の合体攻撃)

Uryu is having a tough time fighting against Privaron Espada Cirucci, whose whip attacks are ever changing.
name: Ishida & Pesche, the United Attack of Friendship
